annotation.TEXT: What, someone drained all the water? How is that even possible? And how would Mario even go about putting the water back?
That was me derpin', but at least I had already revealed this flower, so as long as I don't get hit again immediately, I should be alright.
Hi, Yoshi!
Hello, this is SomeGuy712x, and welcome to...
Space-time rewind count: 1
Push!
Fish!
Goal tape average so far: 40 / 1 = 40 stars each.
Umm... I was expecting lots of coins to appear, but maybe I did something wrong.
Oh, man. I guess all the water really has been drained. Alright, so my level choices right now are Yoshi's House, 1-A Dark Sumo Hills, and 1-1 Teal Grassland.
Well, let's start with Yoshi's House as usual.
Oh, hey! Thanks for warping my springboard over here for me, Sumo Guy!
Looks like I can fly normally. Well, that's cool.
Alright, I think I'll do one more level today, and that level's obviously gonna be 1-1 Teal Grassland. (BTW, waffledoctor87 already made a video of this level. Click here to see it.)
Going up! (And yeah, I'm kind of ignoring that berry for no particular reason.)
Hmm... I'm guessing that's how I was supposed to reach that fudge stripe cookie that was up there.
Okay, that was interesting. Alright, enough fooling around. I'm low enough on time as it is, and I'm sure I don't really need the springboard.
I wonder if maybe the camera should be made to scroll up here. That fudge stripe cookie was half off the screen there.
Also, these arches aren't teal either. Now, I could do another "science" with that pipe, but I'm not gonna bother.
I wonder if I was supposed to use the P-switch in here...
Huh, so the white dotted outline shows where a hidden coin block is, but the hidden 1-up block has no such hint to go with it.
Okay, that is a really clever use of tile 1F0, to allow the Sumo Guy to move much farther than usual like that!
Uh, oh! There's cutoff under the left side of the bush there! This hack's not gonna... Seriously, that joke's been done to death, hasn't it?
Aw, waffledoctor87 removed switchpalacecorner and replaced him with an unbreakable turn block.
Ha-HA! Got it!
So, can I not reach that fudge stripe cookie from there? Man, I hope I wasn't supposed to bounce off that guy while he was in midair... Oh, there's a springboard. Okay.
Oh, I just noticed the angled corners on the ground there. I don't think they're actually slopes though.
I see that the pizzelle physician is still going with the fudge stripe cookie graphics for the Yoshi coins.
Nuts. Hit Start slightly too early to be able to start with a free coin that time.
Yep, there's a Sumo Duder already.
...Mario's Quest for the Water, by waffledoctor87, the maker of Super Tweak World!
Aw, it's so sad that the fish have no place to swim now that the water's all gone.
I know that there's something in that turn block there, but I need a shell to hit it with.
Alright, that's the fifth fudge stripe cookie in this level. Very good.
Well, those munchers are real, and for some reason I can climb on certain parts of this plaid pattern here, which I kind of discovered by accident.
Go, my #FFFF00 ! blocks, and fill the world with your #FFFF00-ness!
DOUBLE KILL! Too bad I couldn't kill all three simultaneously.
Oh, what the?
Okay, there's a light blue ! block...
Up here we find a dozen coins and a fudge stripe cookie.
I wonder why Nintendo never programmed sliding koopas to stop at walls/pipes/etc. while they're sliding...
Well, I don't know... Water levels tend to be boring, so I'm fine with there being no water. But... I suppose we ought to go investigate anyway.
Goal tape average so far: 80 / 2 = 40 stars each.
Yep! Totally figured that would happen! However, since I declared "science" ahead of time for this, I'll just rewind to before that happened now...
I saw a dotted block outline back over here...
I was kind of expecting to come out of that cannon. However, I kinda want my springboard.

waffledoctor87, you might want to take a look at the original SMW's Chocolate Island 1 in Lunar Magic (level 022) to see how Nintendo made use of the invisible "warp hole" sprite to prevent that from being possible with the last pipe cannon in the level.
Whoa! I didn't expect that Sumo Bro. to just fall like that! I'm glad he didn't hit me! Yeah, I'd say that's a justified light blue ! block warning.
I see a half-visible fudge stripe cookie up there.
Hmm... I have a feeling that I can do something with this pipe. I'm declaring "science" right now.
Yep, if I jump properly into it, I can end up within the pipe, and that also means...
Even the Fire Flower looks teal now. However, one thing that's definitely not teal is that Deadly Acid of Death™ down there. Fortunately, it doesn't look like I can fall into it.
Yep, it's teal alright. (I think this color is teal, anyway.)
Science count: 1
Alright, so next time, I'll be playing through 1-2 Triangle Skies, and probably the level after that, and maybe the level after that to wrap up world 1. To be continued... Yo!
Okay, so I've got this yellow P-switch here, and there's some oddly-placed objects...
Whoa, a cape already?! I was expecting maybe another flower, but you're actually giving me a cape in the first level, waffledoctor87? Is cape flight nerfed in any way?
40 again. That's par for the course, I guess. I wonder if I can keep getting nothing but 40s through this entire hack...

Oh, what the? ...Right. Items that have been carried through pipes behave oddly when it comes to Sumo Bro. fire. I did a "Random Moment" video regarding that a long time ago... (Click here to see it.)
Whoa, careful. Okay, so I've got this P-switch. Now I wonder where I should use it...
Now, it doesn't appear that the title demo is any different, so let's just get this game started...
Well, that Lava Lotus is obviously on a 1F0 dirt tile. It's in a position where I can perhaps slide-kill it, though...

UPDATE: I don't know how I didn't notice this at first, but the first room's gimmick was just like the gimmick from that "Photoshop Plains" / "Trimmed World" level in Super Marina World. (Click here to see it.)
That of course unlocks the path leading to the Yellow Switch Palace, but does it have a different name here?
Aha! There's the last fudge stripe cookie! Hopefully this hack will do far better than Bowser Jr.'s Adventure when it comes to those!
...Yep, Yoshi spits fireballs.
I'm gonna go with 1-A Dark Sumo Hills, since it's where YI1 would normally be. Let me guess... It's got Sumo Bros. in it, right?

Well, there's the goal already. Wow, I still have tons of time left, which is unusual for me. (Actually, looking back, this level's timer reset to 400 every time I went into a pipe cannon. I wonder why you set it that way, waffledoctor87?)
And, there's the goal! I think I'll use the springboard to help me reach the top of the goal, since I don't want to change either of my power ups.
Well, I'm not sure what the deal was with that first room, but if I missed something major (like if I was supposed to use the P-switch in this room instead), let me know!
Apparently I had already collected at least 30 coins in this level, so I got a 1-up from that star block.
Well, the place doesn't look as green as it usually does, but otherwise, it's not any different from usual, so let's go somewhere else now.
Huh, so light blue ! blocks warn me of possible trolling, eh? Well, I'll keep that in mind.
Yeah, it does. Now, I believe #FFFF00 is the color yellow, and it's also the number 16,776,920 when converted to decimal (so maybe I could've made the "16 million switch palaces" joke again.)
Whoops. I meant to eat that berry there, not do part of a berry-related glitch which is meaningless because I didn't do the other part of the glitch first.
Aha, a vine!
Now, this shell may look greenish, but I'm pretty sure it's actually got the properties of a red one, so...
